				<td colspan="2"><span>Your card is a GF4, and GF4 chipsets do not support DirectX 9. While DX9 compatibility is not required to play EverQuest, it may be causing problems anyway. Unfortunately, replacing a graphics 'card' on a laptop is not easy. I'm not an expert, but I'm pretty sure it's an integrated type deal, soldered onto the motherboard and possibly using shared system RAM in place of video RAM. Obviously, a normal graphics card will not fit into a laptop any way you try. Some experts may be able to replace the card, but that would be costly and probably risky (void warranty, etc). </span></td>
